    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Bhel Puri is a tangy and spicy Indian street food snack made with puffed rice, vegetables, chutneys, and sev. It's crunchy, flavorful, and easy to make.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>15 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>2 cups puffed rice (murmura)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup chopped onion</li>
        <li>1/2 cup chopped tomato</li>
        <li>1/4 cup boiled potato (cubed)</li>
        <li>2 tbsp green chutney</li>
        <li>2 tbsp tamarind chutney</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp chaat masala</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp finely chopped coriander</li>
        <li>1/2 cup sev</li>
        <li>Lemon juice to taste</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a large bowl, mix puffed rice, chopped vegetables, and boiled potatoes.</li>
        <li>Add both chutneys, chaat masala, salt, and lemon juice. Mix gently.</li>
        <li>Top with sev and fresh coriander just before serving.</li>
        <li>Serve immediately for maximum crunch.</li>
    </ol>
